pieabsasqmmivodghecsosyogslqbanivgaofsmo page 556 In aviation, reference datum height (RDH) is the height of a point, located above the intersection of the runway centre line and the threshold, through which the downward extended straight portion of the glide path passes.[1] It is usually found on the aerodrome instrument approach charts. See also[edit] Vertical datum ICAO recommendations on use of the International System of Units References[edit] ^ Instrument Landing System Reference Datum Height Eurocontrol.int This aviation-related article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. v t e contentType 24 text/html; charset=UTF-8 url 56 https://en.wikipedia.org:443/wiki/Reference_datum_height responseCode 3 200 